# Pin Connections (NodeMCU ESP8266)

1. DHT11 Sensor

* VCC → 3.3V
* GND → GND
* Data → GPIO5 (D1)

2. Soil Moisture Sensor

* VCC → 3.3V
* GND → GND
* Output → A0 (Analog Pin)

3. DS18B20 Sensor

* VCC → 3.3V
* GND → GND
* Data → GPIO4 (D2)
* Pull-up Resistor: 4.7kΩ between VCC and Data

4. LDR Sensor (Voltage Divider)

* One end → 3.3V
* Other end → A0 (via 10kΩ resistor to GND)

5. Relay Module

* VCC → 5V
* GND → GND
* IN → GPIO14 (D5)

6. Water Pump (via Relay/TIP122)

* Controlled using Relay or TIP122 transistor
* External 12V supply

7. LED Strip (via TIP122)

* Controlled via GPIO signal
* Powered using 12V supply

8. Power Connections

* 12V Adapter → Pump + LED
* 7805 Regulator → 5V output for modules
* NodeMCU powered via USB or regulated supply
